{
  "version": "6.0",
  "description": "This diagram illustrates how Objectify works. A user provides a diagram image, which is sent to the Claude Vision API along with a structured system prompt. The AI analyzes the image and produces a JSON specification describing all visual elements. This spec is loaded into the Web Editor, where a Schema Parser converts it into React Flow nodes and edges. The interactive React Flow Canvas allows the user to manipulate the diagram using editing tools: a Guide System for alignment, a Context Menu for styling, and a Command Bar for text-based commands. All changes are tracked in an Undo/Redo stack. The edited diagram can be exported back to JSON, which can be re-imported for further editing.",
